title: wgpu integration example fails to build in release mode
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues.

### Is this issue related to iced?

- [X] My hardware is compatible and my graphics drivers are up-to-date.

### What happened?

The existing [wgpu integration example](https://github.com/iced-rs/iced/tree/master/examples/integration) on the latest master branch fails to build in release mode due to unexpected trait issues.
I'm honestly confused by this as I have no idea why the debug version vs release would be so different to cause these errors.

### What is the expected behavior?

The example should compile in release mode just like it does in debug.

### Version

master

### Operating System

Linux
